-- Japan May Permit Central Bank to Cut Asset Purchase Losses, Nikkei Says
-- B y   P e t e r   J .   B r e n n a n
-- 2010-11-09T20:12:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/japan-may-permit-central-bank-to-cut-asset-purchase-losses-nikkei-says.html
Japan’s Ministry of Finance may
permit the central bank to reduce contributions to the national
treasury should it incur losses in its 5 trillion yen ($61.2
billion) asset purchase program, Nikkei English News said,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Finance Minister Yoshihiko Noda may “soon” make an
official announcement, Nikkei said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  